# {{LOOP_NAME}}

Scaffolded via `bl new junit-basic`. A JUnit5-gated bounded loop: an agent
edits `seed/Example.java` until the JUnit Platform Console Standalone
launcher exits 0, or the loop halts at `bounds.yaml`'s `max_iterations`.

## Files

- `loop.yaml` — the manifest (name, gate, runner, bounds). `gate.kind:
  command` runs the JUnit console-launcher directly (no Maven/Gradle
  needed) — see below.
- `bounds.yaml` — safety bounds (max iterations, no-progress window, etc).
- `PROMPT.md` — the task spec given to the agent. Edit this first.
- `STATE.md` — cross-lap memory, populated automatically.
- `seed/` — the workspace the agent edits (`Example.java`) plus the gate
  anchor test (`ExampleTest.java`, don't edit).
- `cassettes/default.json` — a keyless, deterministic stub-agent recording
  used by `bl run` (via `runner.default: stub` in `loop.yaml`).
- `run.sh` / `wreck.sh` — standalone bash versions of the loop that need no
  engine at all: `run.sh` is gated, `wreck.sh` deliberately removes the gate
  to show why gating matters.

## JUnit without a build tool

There is no Maven/Gradle dependency here. The gate command (and `run.sh`/
`wreck.sh`) fetch the official, single-jar **JUnit Platform Console
Standalone** launcher (`org.junit.platform:junit-platform-console-standalone`)
directly from Maven Central on first use, verify its sha256 checksum, and
cache it at `~/.cache/bounded-loops/junit/` — every later lap and every
other `junit-basic` loop on the same machine reuses the cached jar, so the
fetch happens at most once.

## Requirements

- A JDK (11+) with `javac`/`java` on `PATH`. If you installed OpenJDK via
  Homebrew, it is keg-only and not linked onto the default `PATH` — export
  it first: `export PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/openjdk/bin:$PATH"` (`run.sh`/
  `wreck.sh` already do this defensively; `bl run`'s `gate.kind: command`
  command does too).
- `curl` and `shasum` (both standard on macOS/Linux) for the one-time jar
  fetch.

## Quickstart

```bash
cd {{LOOP_NAME}}
bl run .                 # via the bounded-loops engine (keyless stub runner)
./run.sh                 # or standalone, no engine required
```

Replace `PROMPT.md`, `seed/`, and `cassettes/default.json` with your own
task once you're ready to move past the starter example.
